Crunchies Fried Chicken Limited has celebrated Children’s Day with over N10m worth of meal opportunities and discounted meal vouchers for the children who visited its outlets on May 27, 2022. A statement by the organisation said the free meal opportunities and discounted meal vouchers gave a lot of children the chance to join in the Children’s Day celebrations in all Crunchies Fried Chicken outlets. Likewise, the fast-food company celebrated the day with some orphanages in Aba, Abia State, and showered them with gifts of love. The Managing Director/CEO, Crunchies Fried Chicken Limited, Mrs Muka Ohaeji, said, “Children’s Day is a special event to recognise and celebrate children and today we are celebrating them. Our children are the jewels of society and the onus is on us to pay special attention to their physical, educational and social wellbeing. “We pride ourselves as a children-friendly brand, which made us consider the need to provide kiddies play area in all our outlets for these little ones to feel good. We celebrate our children today and will continue to do our bit to ensure they have a beautiful tomorrow.” The Head of Marketing & Public Relations, Crunchies Fried Chicken, Mr Babatunde Folawewo, added that the vouchers would be issued from the 26th to the 28th of May, 2022 in different touch points and would be valid for redemption on June 4th, 2022 across all Crunchies Fried Chicken outlets. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com